<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-12T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-12T08:00:00-05:00" n="623" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d623">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2934</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-12T13:00:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 12, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.56 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2737. Following from Stockholm: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>219, October 11, 1 p.m. <persName corresp="#p_WCWB1">Webster</persName><note n="1" xml:id="d623fn1">
                                        <persName corresp="#p_WCWB1">Capt. William B.
                                            Webster</persName>, member of the American Red Cross
                                        Commission to Russia.</note> arrived yesterday with 7
                                    Americans, 31 British, 29 French, including <persName corresp="#p_LRHB1">Lockhart</persName>,
                                        <persName>Ward</persName>, <persName>Robin P.
                                        Lavergne</persName> and consular and military staffs from
                                    Moscow. Forty-five British and 5 French still in fortress
                                    Petrograd. <persName corresp="#p_WMA1">Wardwell</persName> and
                                        <persName>Andrews</persName> hope to come out shortly by
                                    boat. Everything all right at Embassy. Rumor Kalamatiano shot in
                                    Moscow. Seventeen more Americans arrive to-day. <persName corresp="#p_WS1">Whitehouse</persName>.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Archangel notified.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>